<subSubSection id="F6B8652FEE4FFF9B6B8DD7EEFCC1F5B8" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="BE1D36A4EE4FFF9B6B8DD7EEFCC1F5B8" blockId="9.[151,1436,782,2007]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">
<emphasis id="8CD6EAB6EE4FFF9B6B8DD7EEFE16F59F" bold="true" box="[198,510,1710,1736]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Distribution and habitat</emphasis>
:—Known from white sand areas in the lowlands around Manaus in 
<collectingCountry id="C6B57634EE4FFF9B6E07D7EEFA7FF59F" box="[1356,1431,1710,1736]" name="Brazil" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Brazil</collectingCountry>
; partly disturbed primary forests on well drained ground.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="F6B8652FEE4FFF986B8DD7BBFD97F3A8" lastPageId="10" lastPageNumber="11" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="BE1D36A4EE4FFF9B6B8DD7BBFEE4F4DD" blockId="9.[151,1436,782,2007]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">
<emphasis id="8CD6EAB6EE4FFF9B6B8DD7BBFEA2F442" bold="true" box="[198,330,1787,1813]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Discussion</emphasis>
:— 
<taxonomicName id="79A24D27EE4FFF9B6A24D7BCFD48F442" box="[367,672,1788,1813]" class="Liliopsida" family="Marantaceae" genus="Monotagma" kingdom="Plantae" order="Zingiberales" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="breviscapum">
<emphasis id="8CD6EAB6EE4FFF9B6A24D7BCFD48F442" box="[367,672,1788,1813]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Monotagma breviscapum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is easily recognized by its trailing rhizomes and very short synflorescence peduncle. It is most similar to 
<taxonomicName id="79A24D27EE4FFF9B69A1D663FC72F46B" authorityName="Hagberg" authorityYear="1990" box="[746,922,1827,1852]" class="Liliopsida" family="Marantaceae" genus="Monotagma" kingdom="Plantae" order="Zingiberales" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="vaginatum">
<emphasis id="8CD6EAB6EE4FFF9B69A1D663FC72F46B" box="[746,922,1827,1852]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">M. vaginatum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, from which it differs by the very short synflorescence peduncle, the presence of proper petioles (vs. absence), and the exannulate pulvini (vs. annulate).
</paragraph>
